comment_data.body: @duzenko what the version of Android Studio and Flutter plugin do you use? Is it still so?

>

> @duzenko what the version of Android Studio and Flutter plugin do you use? Is it still so?

```
[√] Android Studio (version 3.5)
    • Android Studio at C:\tools\android-studio
    • Flutter plugin version 40.0.2
    • Dart plugin version 191.8423
    • Java version OpenJDK Runtime Environment (build 1.8.0_202-release-1483-b03)
```

Still inactive for our business app. In new empty apps it's ok.
@stevemessick - Should issue https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/pull/3909 fix this problem too?
@terrylucas I think so. But an old project may have bad metadata.

Could you re-create your old project file it probably contains stale or bad metadata that wasn't conversion between either various version of AS or metadata that the plugin add.  This should fix the problem and hopefully won't happen again.  If this problem still occurs re-open this issue.

- This issue is not resolved. Please reopen the ticket.

- How do I re-create the project? Please link to the step-by-step walkthrough.

- Are you sure this is the end-user's problem and there is nothing to fix on your side?

Here are two links on what is a project in IntelliJ/Flutter and how to create a project from existing source code.

[What is an .idea directory](https://rider-support.jetbrains.com/hc/en-us/articles/207097529-What-is-the-idea-folder-
)
[Creating a Flutter project from existing source code](https://flutter.dev/docs/development/tools/android-studio#creating-a-new-project-from-existing-source-code)

Please advise
